        <h1 class="city-heading-xl">Apply for a Women’s Land Army or Women’s Timber Corps veterans badge</h1>

        <p class="city-body-l">You can get the veterans badge if you are a veteran of either the Women’s Land Army (<abbr title="Women's Land Army">WLA</abbr>) or the Women’s Timber Corps (<abbr title="Women's Timber Corps">WTC</abbr>).</p>

        <h2 class="city-heading-l">Eligibility</h2>

        <p class="city-body-m">You’ll get the badge if you served during World War 1 or World War 2, or at any time up until the corps were disbanded in 1950.</p>

        <p class="city-body-m">You can apply for a badge if you are the spouse or family member of a deceased veteran, but only if they died after 6 December 2007 (when the badge was issued).</p>

        <h2 class="city-heading-l">How to apply</h2>

        <p class="city-body-m">Fill in the <a href="/government/publications/women-s-land-army-and-timber-corps-veterans-badge-application-form" class="city-link"><abbr title="Women's Land Army">WLA</abbr> and <abbr title="Women's Timber Corps">WTC</abbr> veterans badge application form.</a></p>

        <p class="city-body-m">You’ll need to give your date of birth, approximate dates of service in the <abbr title="Women's Land Army">WLA</abbr> or <abbr title="Women's Timber Corps">WTC</abbr>, and the location at which you (or your family member or spouse) were stationed.</p>

        <p class="city-body-m">Send your form by email or post to Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs (<abbr title="Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs">Defra</abbr>).</p>


        <p class="city-body-m"><strong><abbr title="Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs">Defra</abbr></strong>
        <a href="mailto:womenslandarmy@defra.gsi.gov.uk" class="city-link">womenslandarmy@defra.gsi.gov.uk</a><br>
        Telephone: 0208 026 3078<br>
        <a href="/call-charges" class="city-link">Find out about call charges</a></p>


        <p class="city-body-m">

        Women’s Land Army Team
        <br>Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs
        <br>Area 1A
        <br>Nobel House
        <br>17 Smith Square
        <br>London
        <br>SW1P 3JR
        <br>
        </p>

        <h2 class="city-heading-l">After you’ve applied</h2>

        <p class="city-body-m">You’ll receive your badge within 4 weeks or you’ll be contacted if you need to provide more information.</p>
